The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:46 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.4 percent to 13,257.13, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.3 percent to 1,613.67.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , Colombiaâ€™s biggest lender, fell
for a seventh session. The company said it plans to raise as
much as 1.66 trillion pesos ($883 million) in a share sale that
began Jan. 6. Shares fell 0.6 percent to 26,800 pesos and have
lost 5.9 percent since Jan. 2.  Oil companies  dropped after U.S. crude and fuel supplies
climbed more than analysts estimated amid concern that a
contracting German economy may drag Europe into recession.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in Colombia, fell 2.4 percent to
1,605 pesos.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PREC)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, fell 1.4 percent
to 39,460 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
